{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop DWP additional spouse payments in overseas-registered polygamous marriages",
        "additional_details": "We believe this should not be UK tax-payer funded.",
        "background": "From April 2026, the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) permits people in the UK in specific, legally recognized, overseas-registered polygamous marriages to receive additional benefit payments, with rates for \"additional spouses\" increasing to \u00a3125.25 per week. ",
